The paper deals with the problem of ranking items based on noisy comparisons, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes algorithms and lower bounds for sample complexity, which are relevant to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI) concepts related to noisy comparisons.
